ようび = youbi = Day
曜日 = -yōbi = Day
月曜日 げつようび getsuyoubi = Monday
火曜日 かようび kayoubi = Tuesday	
水曜日 すいようび suiyoubi = Wednesday
木曜日 もくようび mokuyoubi	= Thursday
金曜日 きんようび kinyoubi = Friday	
土曜日 どようび doyoubi = Saturday	
日曜日 にちようび nichiyoubi = Sunday	

月 = Getsu / Tsuki = Moon
火 = Ka = Fire
水 = Sui / Mizu = Water
木 = moku = Wood
金 = kin = gold
土 = do = soil
日 = Nichi = Sun / Day 

今日 きょう kyou	= today
昨日 きのう kinou = yesterday
一昨日 おととい ototoi	= the day before yesterday
明日 あした ashita	= tomorrow
明後日 あさって = asatte	the day after tomorrow
一日 いちにち ichinichi	= all day long
週 しゅう shuu = week
今週 こんしゅう konshuu	= this week
先週 せんしゅう senshuu =	last week
来週 らいしゅう raishuu	= next week
月 げつ getsu	= month
今月 こんげつ kongetsu	= this month
先月 せんげつ sengetsu	= last month
来月 らいげつ raigetsu = next month
年 ねん nen	= year
今年 ことし kotoshi	= this year
去年 きょねん kyonen = last year
来年 らいねん rainen = next year

"""
the particle に (ni) is used for words depicting time, place, and the direction of action. This means that days of the week will almost always be followed by the particle
  金曜日にライブへ行きました” (Kinyoubi ni raibu e ikimashita). =  “I went to a concert on Friday”
the subject marker が (ga) and the topic marker は (wa) will take precedence if the day of the week is the subject and/or topic of the sentence.
  “金曜日がライブの日です” (Kinyoubi ga raibu no hi desu) = “Friday is the day of the concert,”
if a day is used as a possessive, it will take the particle の (no).
  “金曜日のライブはすごかった!” (Kinyoubi no raibu wa sugokatta!) = “Friday’s concert was awesome!”
native speakers often drop the particles from days of the week and other date-related words. You could say,
  “金曜日, ライブへ行きました” (Kinyoubi, raibu e ikimashita) and still be correct.
"""
火曜日のランチはかならずパスタです. Kayoubi no ranchi wa kanarazu pasta desu. = Tuesday’s lunch is always spaghetti. 
金曜日に試験があります. Kinyoubi ni shaken ga arimasu. = I have a test on Friday.
明日が私の誕生日です. Ashita ga watashi no tanjoubi desu. = Tomorrow is my birthday.
来週, うちのおばさんの家に行きます. Raishuu, uchi no obsa-san no ie ni ikimasu. = We’re going to my aunt’s house next week.
月曜日にデートがあります. Getsuyoubi ni deeto ga arimasu. = I have a date on Monday.


